task.summary: Changed processing.py to run as a single thread for all jobs (and fixed resulting bugs) Started writing unit tests
Changed scaling function to accept a list of cropped files returned by autocrop
Fixed the scaling call and debug print statement
Changed resampler to keep image in memory for testing on Windows
Fixed scaling - was autocropping even though it had manually cropped already
Changed output directory autofill to "processed_recons" (added underscore)
Started writing a test bed with various example data
Fixed bug where scaling would fail if no cropping was performed
Ubuntu keeps messing up, haven't made any actual changes
Fixed z-project callback issue, and changed status string to be more informative
Z-projections only need to be computed once - previous ones are loaded back in (for the same scan only)
Manual cropbox now draggable by corners, making resizing easier
Added "force" option to z-project, which will recompute regardless of whether a previous zp exists
